        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">What is the 50/30/20 Budget Rule?</h2>
        
        <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
          The 50/30/20 budget rule is a simple and effective method for managing your finances. It divides your after-tax income into three categories:
        </p>

        <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-300 mb-6">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-[#d4ff2a] font-bold mt-1">50% for Needs:</span>
            <span>Essential expenses like housing, utilities, groceries, transportation, insurance</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-[#d4ff2a] font-bold mt-1">30% for Wants:</span>
            <span>Non-essential expenses like dining out, entertainment, hobbies, subscriptions</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-[#d4ff2a] font-bold mt-1">20% for Savings:</span>
            <span>Emergency fund, retirement, investments, debt payments beyond minimums</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

